        <h1>Corporate Conquests</h1>
        <p class="intro">
          Leveraged deals, surprise layoffs, and theatrical turnarounds became Monty's signature moves during the
          eighties buyout boom.
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main class="container">
      <section class="cards-grid expanded-grid" aria-label="Corporate conquest details">
        <article class="card">
          <div class="card-link">
            <h2>The Cutlery Incident</h2>
            <p>
              Monty replaced sterling forks with plastic for a week to expose “wasteful habits.” The VP who complained
              first became the example of fiscal discipline.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <div class="card-link">
            <h2>Morale Rebranding</h2>
            <p>
              He coined “curated austerity” to describe layoffs paired with catered motivational breakfasts. Share price
              rose; employee loyalty did not.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <div class="card-link">
            <h2>Silver Parachutes</h2>
            <p>
              Executives who survived restructuring received engraved parachute pins signifying their loyalty. Several now
              sell for high prices at discreet auctions.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="page-footer">
